  "title": "Foundation: Vite + React 18 + MV3 extension shell",
  "type": "feature",
  "userRequest": "A Chrome extension for managing browser tabs and browser history",
  "description": "Stood up a clean modern foundation for the TabCommand MV3 extension, replacing the 2022 Create-React-App/React-17 build (kept read-only on main at ../tabcommand as the reference spec). Build now uses Vite 5 + @vitejs/plugin-react + @crxjs/vite-plugin, emitting a Chrome-loadable bundle to build/ with no --openssl-legacy-provider hack. The React entry mounts via React 18 createRoot (StrictMode preserved) into an intentionally empty App shell (navy sidebar + TabCommand logo + a 'modern rebuild in progress' placeholder, zero chrome.* calls). manifest.json, the 667-line service_worker.js background engine, and the popup/ launcher were ported verbatim. Test stack is Vitest + React Testing Library (replacing React-18-incompatible enzyme); ESLint 9 flat-config is the lint gate. codeyam was wired to the chrome-extension-react stack: vitest runner + eslint static check, app on port 3000 (Vite honors the proxy-injected PORT on IPv4), Desktop 1440x900 capture. The full-page app index.html is registered as an explicit build input since the popup opens it dynamically. The project dropped type:module (configs renamed to .mjs) so the editor's CommonJS capture scripts run. Per the strict finalize gate, real Vitest coverage was added for all 23 logic-bearing functions in the verbatim-ported service_worker.js (19) and popup.js (4) via a sandboxed-load harness, and each was registered in the glossary. Out of scope (later plans): chrome.storage layer + in-app shim + seeding, Tabs/Labels/drag-drop/Search/Load/UrlDetails/ImportExport, modernizing the worker. Acceptance: npm run build produces a loadable build/, dev server renders the shell with no client errors, 40/40 tests pass, lint clean, session-finalize green.",
